---
type: "no-sidebar"
title: "freshers-week"
additional_css: ["photoswipe/photoswipe.css", "photoswipe/default-skin/default-skin.css"]
additional_js: ["photoswipe/photoswipe.min.js", "photoswipe/photoswipe-ui-default.min.js"]
---

<div class="wrapper">
    <div class="container" id="main">
        <article id="content">
            <header>
                <h2>Freshers Week</h2>
                <p>
                    Freshers Week is essentially Welcome Week at the University of Birmingham for new students. Students are introduced to the University with induction lectures and all Student Societies run a variety of events during Freshers Week to enable the new students
                    to meet like minded people and make new friends.
                </p>
            </header>

            <p>
                The Islamic Society organises an incredible itinerary of Freshers Week events every single year and this year is no different! We have a great list of events which you can see on the poster below. Itâ€™s a great opportunity to build new friendships and
                enjoy yourself in the fund and welcoming atmosphere the Islamic Society provides.
            </p>

            <div class="gallery-preview">
                <%= tag :img, :src => "/images/fw-16-17/p1.jpg" %>
                <div class="gp-content">
                    <h1><i class="fa fa-picture-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Gallery</h1>
                    <p>
						A week to meet like minded people and make new friends
						through various events.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="gp-overlay">
                    <div class="gp-button">
                        <i class="fa fa-search" data-gallery="gallery" aria-hidden="true"></i>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <p>
                We finish off Freshers Week with our annual Freshers Dinner where we serve a 3 course meal and host entertainment at a hall in Birmingham to allow new students to socialise and have fun with their newly found friends. You can view the event page using
                the following link: [Freshers Dinner Facebook event page link]
            </p>

            <div class="block">
                <h3>If you have any questions about Freshers Week 2017 please email</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Anas Abu (<a href="mailto:vicebrother@ubisoc.co.uk">vicebrother@ubisoc.co.uk</a>)</li>
                    <li>Salma Abdallah (<a href="vicesister@ubsico.co.uk">vicesister@ubsico.co.uk</a>)</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </article>
    </div>
</div>

<!-- GALLERY -->
<div id="gallery">
	<% for i in 1..7 %>
		<%= tag :img, :src => "/images/fw-16-17/p#{i}.jpg", :"data-size" => "2048x1365" %>
	<% end %>
</div>

<!-- Root element of PhotoSwipe. Must have class pswp. -->
<div class="pswp" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-hidden="true">

    <!-- Background of PhotoSwipe.
         It's a separate element as animating opacity is faster than rgba(). -->
    <div class="pswp__bg"></div>

    <!-- Slides wrapper with overflow:hidden. -->
    <div class="pswp__scroll-wrap">

        <!-- Container that holds slides.
            PhotoSwipe keeps only 3 of them in the DOM to save memory.
            Don't modify these 3 pswp__item elements, data is added later on. -->
        <div class="pswp__container">
            <div class="pswp__item"></div>
            <div class="pswp__item"></div>
            <div class="pswp__item"></div>
        </div>

        <!-- Default (PhotoSwipeUI_Default) interface on top of sliding area. Can be changed. -->
        <div class="pswp__ui pswp__ui--hidden">

            <div class="pswp__top-bar">

                <!--  Controls are self-explanatory. Order can be changed. -->

                <div class="pswp__counter"></div>

                <button class="pswp__button pswp__button--close" title="Close (Esc)"></button>

                <button class="pswp__button pswp__button--share" title="Share"></button>

                <button class="pswp__button pswp__button--fs" title="Toggle fullscreen"></button>

                <button class="pswp__button pswp__button--zoom" title="Zoom in/out"></button>

                <!-- Preloader demo http://codepen.io/dimsemenov/pen/yyBWoR -->
                <!-- element will get class pswp__preloader--active when preloader is running -->
                <div class="pswp__preloader">
                    <div class="pswp__preloader__icn">
                        <div class="pswp__preloader__cut">
                            <div class="pswp__preloader__donut"></div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="pswp__share-modal pswp__share-modal--hidden pswp__single-tap">
                <div class="pswp__share-tooltip"></div>
            </div>

            <button class="pswp__button pswp__button--arrow--left" title="Previous (arrow left)">
            </button>

            <button class="pswp__button pswp__button--arrow--right" title="Next (arrow right)">
            </button>

            <div class="pswp__caption">
                <div class="pswp__caption__center"></div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
